<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214045>
    dc:creator "Felder, Darryl L.", "Lemaitre, Rafael" ;
    dc:date "2012" ;
    dc:title "A new species of the hermit crab genus Areopaguriste s Rahayu & McLaughlin, 2010 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura: Diogenidae) discovered in the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef of Belize, Caribbean Sea" ;
    bibo:endPage "79" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "67" ;
    bibo:volume "3480" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214046>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214047>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214048>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214049>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214050>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214051> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214046>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Areopaguristes tudgei n. sp., Carrie Bow Cay, Belize: a, c – e, h, male paratype, 2.1 mm ,, February 8 (USNM 1156993); b, f, g, i, female paratype, 2.1 mm, February 4 (USNM 1156991). a, shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; b, anterior portion of shield, dorsal view; c, male left first pleopod, posterior view; d, left second pleopod, posterior view; e, male left third pleopod, posterior view; f, female left first pleopod, posterior view; g, female left third pleopod, posterior view; h, uropods and telson, dorsal view; i, telson, dorsal view. Scales equal 0.5 mm (a, b, e, h, i), 0.2 mm (c, d, f, g)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214046/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214047>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Areopaguristes tudgei n. sp.: male paratype, 2.1 mm, Carrie Bow Cay, Belize, February 8 (USNM 1156993). Left mouthparts, internal view: a, mandible; b, maxillule; c, maxilla; d, first maxilliped; e, second maxilliped; f, third maxilliped, g, ischium of same with crista dentata. Scales equal 0.1 mm (a – d, g), and 0.2 mm (e, f)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214047/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214048>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Areopaguristes tudgei n. sp.: male paratype, 2.1 mm, Carrie Bow Cay, Belize, February 8 (USNM 1156993). Chelipeds, all dorsal view except f (mesial), and c (ventral); a, b, showing approximate density of setation; c – f, with setae omitted. a, d, left; b, e, right; c, fingers of same; f, right. Scale equals 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214048/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214049>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Areopaguristes tudgei n. sp.: male paratype, 2.1 mm, Carrie Bow Cay, Belize, February 8 (USNM 1156993). a, second right pereopod with plumose setae, lateral view; b, dactyl of same, mesial view; c, same pereopod with setae omitted, mesial view; d, third right pereopod, lateral view; e, dactyl of same; f, propodus and dactyl of right fourth pereopod, lateral view; g, propodus and dactyl of right fifth pereopod, lateral view. Scales equal 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214049/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214050>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Areopaguristes tudgei n. sp.: male paratype, 2.1 mm, Carrie Bow Cay, Belize, February 8 (USNM 1156993). Sternites XI – XIV, coxae of chelipeds and second to fifth pereopods, and anterior portion of pleon with first and second pleopods, ventral view. Scale equals 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214050/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214051>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Areopaguristes tudgei n. sp., Carrie Bow Cay, Belize, February 4: a, female paratype 1.9 mm (ULLZ 12530); b, male paratype 3.0 mm (ULLZ 12576). Scales equal 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214051/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

